news.title: Lodha Developers' net profit rises 86.67% in Q2 FY26
news.para: Lodha Developers announced a significant profit jump of 86.67 percent for the quarter ending September 30, 2025. The company's profit after tax reached ₹789.80 crore. Total income also saw a substantial increase of 44.49 percent. Lodha Developers achieved its full-year business development goal early. The company is on track to meet its pre-sales guidance.

news.title: DLF's net profit dips 14.56% in Q2 FY26
news.para: DLF reported a 14.56% dip in net consolidated profit for Q2 FY26, with profit after tax at ₹1,180.09 crore. The company's total income saw a 3.71% growth, reaching ₹2,261.80 crore. During the quarter, DLF Home Developers redeemed NCDs and the company declared a dividend of ₹6 per equity share.

news.title: Maharashtra charity commissioner orders cancellation of deed to sell Jain trust property to builder
news.para: Pune's charity commissioner has cancelled the sale of a prime 3.5 acre property. The land, owned by a Jain trust, was to be sold to a builder. The community protested the deal. The builder and trust agreed to cancel the sale deed. The builder will receive a full refund. The property currently houses a boarding and a Jain Temple.

news.title: Crafting the future of luxury living
news.para: Set against the vibrant and dynamic backdrop of a rapidly evolving urban landscape, the grand launch of Jade County symbolised a significant new chapter in contemporary and sustainable residential development

news.title: DDA, IIT-Delhi to inspect 'structural incident' in Dwarka's apartment building
news.para: In response to the unsettling explosion-like noise reported at Triveni Apartments in Dwarka, the Delhi Development Authority has teamed up with IIT-Delhi to conduct a thorough investigation. Specialists will delve into the structural integrity of the building, aiming to pinpoint the cause of the disturbance.

news.title: Keppel Corporation's profit jumps 25% during January-September 2025
news.para: Keppel Corporation is basking in financial success as it reveals a stunning 25% profit increase for the first three quarters of the year. The company has seen robust growth in all its divisions, leading to a significant boost in recurring income.

news.title: Bengaluru development body recovers encroached property worth ₹12 crore in BTM Layout
news.para: The Bangalore Development Authority (BDA) has successfully reclaimed a prime 6,629 sqft parcel of land valued at Rs 12.3 crore in BTM 1st Stage. This action, part of a broader initiative, involved demolishing unauthorized compounds and sheds. The BDA vows to continue enforcement operations to protect public lands from encroachment.

news.title: Shriram Properties to jointly develop 0.7 million sq ft project in Pune
news.para: Shriram Properties has entered into a joint development agreement for a 0.7 million sq ft residential project in Hinjewadi, Pune. The project, with a gross development value potential of ₹700 crore, includes apartments, retail, and commercial spaces, further strengthening the company's presence in the thriving Pune market.

news.title: About 42 apply for M-sand production unit in Nagpur district under new policy
news.para: Nagpur district is seeing a strong uptake of the state's artificial sand (M-sand) policy, with 42 industrialists applying to establish production units. The policy aims to reduce river sand extraction and boost industry, offering royalty concessions and other incentives. M-sand, derived from readily available basalt stone, is suitable for various construction applications beyond plastering.

news.title: Sand shortage hits Nagpur metro's construction works across all stretches
news.para: Nagpur Metro's Phase II construction faces delays due to an acute shortage of naturally available sand. MahaMetro has partially halted works across all four stretches as existing stocks are nearly depleted. Officials are exploring alternatives like manufactured sand (M-sand) and crushed sand, with safety tests underway.

news.title: Panel to review Delhi's settlements, pooling, land use
news.para: A dedicated parliamentary committee is delving into the pressing land issues in Delhi. Among the highlighted concerns are the legalising of informal settlements and the advancement of the land pooling policy.

news.title: Dharavi redevelopment project & SRA appointed as special planning authorities for salt pan land
news.para: The Dharavi Redevelopment Project (DRP) and Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA) have been appointed as the special planning authority for the 42.51-acre Jamasp Salt Pan land in Mulund East. This land, part of a larger 256-acre parcel approved for the Dharavi redevelopment, will be used for rental housing for ineligible residents.

news.title: New regulations in Rajasthan restrict certain business activities in residential zones
news.para: Rajasthan's Urban Development and Housing department has prohibited warehousing, wholesale markets, and oil/gas depots in residential zones, effective immediately. These changes, made through amendments to development regulations, aim to bring clarity and consistency to urban land use across various categories, aligning with central government directives for deregulation.

news.title: Kerala government amends building rules, getting permits now easier
news.para: Kerala has introduced significant amendments to its building rules, expanding self-certified permit categories for residential and commercial buildings up to 300 sq m and 250 sq m respectively. Site inspections will now occur post-plinth completion, and setback norms have been eased for small plot owners, aiming for a more transparent and efficient construction approval system.

news.title: Industrialist buys four apartments in Gurugram for ₹380-crore
news.para: A prominent industrialist has purchased four apartments in Gurugram for a staggering ₹380 crore. This deal marks one of the most expensive apartment transactions in India. The buyer, an NCR-based industrialist, initially sought a farmhouse in Lutyens' Delhi. The four interconnected apartments will cover over 35,000 sq ft. Equity investors from Mumbai have also acquired units in the project.

news.title: BMC: Ward level squads are checking if Mumbai construction sites follow guidelines
news.para: The BMC has deployed ward-level squads to monitor construction sites' adherence to air quality guidelines, issuing hundreds of notices in September. This action follows criticism for a delayed warning regarding AQI monitor installation. Officials emphasize the ongoing nature of checks and the process of ensuring quality monitor installations.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt allows Noida authority's nod for extra FAR in sector 107 project
news.para: The UP government has dismissed a revision petition challenging the Noida Authority's decision to grant additional floor area ratio (FAR) to a project developer. The petition, filed by an Apartment Owners Association, was deemed not maintainable as the orders were issued under a different act.

news.title: Aditya Birla Sun Life AMC to raise ₹1,500 crore through realty credit fund
news.para: Aditya Birla Sun Life AMC is launching a Rs 1,500 crore alternative investment fund, ABRECOF-II, to provide senior secured loans to real estate projects. The fund targets predictable, risk-adjusted returns with strong downside protection, focusing on post-approval, brownfield projects by established developers in major Indian cities. It aims for a gross IRR of 16-18% with quarterly coupon payouts.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India's profit surges two-fold to ₹24.93 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: HeidelbergCement India's net profits soared to Rs 24.93 crore for the September quarter of FY26, an impressive double from previous results. This upswing is fueled by an increase in sales volume and better pricing strategies. The company's operational revenue witnessed a substantial boost, as sales volume grew by 9.2 percent.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance's net profit up 1.63% in Q2 FY26
news.para: LIC Housing Finance saw a slight profit increase in the September quarter. Net profit rose to over ₹1,349 crore. Total income also grew. The company expects positive business growth ahead. Disbursements in individual home loans showed a 3% rise. The loan portfolio expanded by 6%.
